headline: Scotiabank upgrades CF Industries to Sector Perform with short ‘played out’
summary: As previously reported, Scotiabank analyst Ben Isaacson upgraded CF Industries (CF) to Sector Perform from Underperform with an unchanged price target of $81. Following a tactical downgrade to Sell in January, the firm argues that the stock’s recent performance over the past few months “suggests our thesis has played out” and notes that it now sees 20% upside to mid-cycle fair value. headline: CF Forms JV With JERA & Mitsui for Low-Carbon Ammonia Production
summary: The joint venture will be structured with CF holding a 40% stake, JERA 35% and Mitsui 25%.
